history.content: I took the class with Parekh last year. The workload doesn’t really change much throughout the semester imo, so you should be fine! I felt like the entire class was almost a review of concepts (e.g. later on they cover Markov Chains for about 1/3 of the class), just more in-depth than 70 did, so it doesn’t feel too different than the first 1/3. The only exception is when they cover Kalman filters for the last week or so, and that’s where I had to spend a lot more time, but only because it was more conceptually difficult (the actual HW and lab workload was the same).

children.subject: My only background was 70, and I forgot most of the material by the time I took 126, so I think I was in the same position as you haha. Either way if you’re finding it relatively manageable right now, I don’t think it’ll change much later in the semester. Although you're only ~1 week in, so it would be best to wait until after you’ve done a few more HWs. I think the first 3 HWs and first lab are pretty representative of the difficulty of the class

Thanks, this is helpful. Another thing to note is that I find probability harder/unnatural than linear algebra calculations / I have to think more to be precise in my answer. @Anonymous Mouse I don't know your background but it's probably just taking 70 and using that as background, but if you've done more than please let me know bc it informs the student answer
